cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - This paper deals with image processing and recognition of sign language gestures, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - Sign language recognition is an important aspect of human-computer interaction, as it enables communication between deaf or hard-of-hearing individuals and computers. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - Sign language recognition involves the processing and interpretation of natural language in a visual form, which falls under the domain of computation and language. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed classification technique, Eigen value weighted Euclidean distance, is a machine learning algorithm. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Sign language recognition involves the processing and analysis of multimedia data, such as images and videos.
